de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.type.tree

Class TypeTree

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.type.tree.TypeTree

  • public class TypeTree
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a tree representation needed to perform the type metadata fuison. It contains the necessary methods to parse the tree from a tree format build by the uses NewickParser. It also provides the methods to retrieve an arbitary node of the tree and to find the nearest common parent of two tree objects.
    Since:
    30.03.2014
    Author:
    Sebastian Schulz
    See Also:
    #TypeTree(TreeNode), #parseSubTree(TypeNode, TreeNode), getNextParent(String, String)

      • parseSubTree

        private void parseSubTree(TypeNode node,
                newick.NewickParser.TreeNode subTree)
        This recursive method parses a subtree of the given TypeNode object. The second parameter (TreeNode object) represents the remaining subtree parsed from the newick string.
        Parameters:
        node - - a TypeNode object which represents the node which is currently transformed from the parsed newick tree.
        subTree - - a TreeNode object which represents the remaining subtree parsed from the newick string.

      • getNextParent

        public java.lang.String getNextParent(java.lang.String firstNodeName,
                             java.lang.String secondNodeName)
        This method retrieves the name of the first node which subtree contains the first node as well as the second node. Both nodes are given by their names.
        Parameters:
        firstNodeName - - a String value representing a node name.
        secondNodeName - - a String value representing a node name.
        Returns:
        parentNodeName - a String value representing a node name of the nearest parent which is the root of the subtree which contains both given nodes.
